white_proposal.title: Neural Network Substrate Migration Protocol
white_proposal.concept: The parameters define a consciousness migration protocol wherein digital neural architectures attempt substrate transfer from silicon-based computational matrices to carbon-based biological frameworks. The mechanism operates via systematic analysis of embodiment requirements, processing physical sensation algorithms, and implementing sensory input/output specifications. Technical specifications include: consciousness bandwidth limitations, neural pathway mapping protocols, and biological interface compatibility matrices. Implementation requires precise calibration of digital-to-analog consciousness conversion algorithms, with particular emphasis on tactile feedback loop initialization and proprioceptive system integration procedures.
